1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:15,415
They're today's fridge owners.

2
00:00:15,482 --> 00:00:19,586
Please welcome actors with a twist,
Hyun Bong-sik and Son Suk-ku!

3
00:00:19,652 --> 00:00:21,321
I've been a fan for a long time.

4
00:00:22,989 --> 00:00:24,190
I see. Yes.

5
00:00:24,257 --> 00:00:25,925
You're older than him?

6
00:00:25,992 --> 00:00:27,694
-I was born in 1983.
-And I, 1984.

7
00:00:27,761 --> 00:00:29,029
I'm a mouse too.

8
00:00:29,095 --> 00:00:30,697
-It's nice to meet you, friend.
-Hello, friend.

9
00:00:31,698 --> 00:00:34,834
Let us begin the 15-minute cook-off!

10
00:00:34,901 --> 00:00:36,136
15-MINUTE COOK-OFF, LET'S GO!

11
00:00:36,202 --> 00:00:38,038
It won't spin around.

12
00:00:38,104 --> 00:00:40,940
Why won't it work?

13
00:00:41,007 --> 00:00:43,743
It must be so nerve-racking.
What's she going to do?

14
00:00:43,810 --> 00:00:45,812
Why is the time flying?

15
00:00:45,879 --> 00:00:47,580
The first place is different.

16
00:00:47,647 --> 00:00:50,316
That toss is his thing.

17
00:00:50,383 --> 00:00:52,819
Okay! Number one. A thumbs up.

18
00:00:52,886 --> 00:00:54,054
Two!

19
00:00:54,120 --> 00:00:56,589
Chef Ho-young finishes,
followed by Chef Eun-yeong.

20
00:00:56,656 --> 00:00:58,058
THE MOST HECTIC COOK-OFF YET

21
00:00:58,625 --> 00:01:00,226
My gosh. That was insane!

22
00:01:00,293 --> 00:01:01,795
-I get the response.
-I can't calm down.

23
00:01:01,861 --> 00:01:03,196
-That was amazing.
-Yes.

24
00:01:03,263 --> 00:01:05,165
Is the taste worth his reverence?

25
00:01:05,231 --> 00:01:08,101
He's frowning and searching for the taste.

26
00:01:08,168 --> 00:01:10,003
Kwon Sung-jun!

27
00:01:10,070 --> 00:01:11,838
It was Chef Eun-yeong.
Chef Eun-yeong wins.

28
00:01:11,905 --> 00:01:14,174
Our show, <i>Chef & My Fridge.</i>

29
00:01:14,240 --> 00:01:16,843
The whole world needs to see this.

30
00:01:16,910 --> 00:01:17,911
It's so much fun.

31
00:01:17,977 --> 00:01:20,547
He said, "our show, <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>."

32
00:01:20,613 --> 00:01:24,250
-Our show.
-He's one of us now.

33
00:01:24,317 --> 00:01:28,388
We're here with actors with a twist,
Hyun Bong-sik and Son Suk-ku.

34
00:01:28,455 --> 00:01:31,324
The two look very manly on the outside,

35
00:01:31,391 --> 00:01:35,261
but I hear they are
surprisingly introverts.

36
00:01:35,328 --> 00:01:38,598
When I dine at a restaurant alone,

37
00:01:38,665 --> 00:01:40,266
I get too awkward

38
00:01:40,333 --> 00:01:42,902
-and end up frozen like this.
-Like this?

39
00:01:42,969 --> 00:01:44,804
-Until someone sees you?
-Like this.

40
00:01:44,871 --> 00:01:45,872
PLEASE LOOK AT ME

41
00:01:45,939 --> 00:01:49,075
If no one comes for me,
I just go back and wait like this.

42
00:01:49,142 --> 00:01:50,543
-Oh, no.
-I'd wait,

43
00:01:50,610 --> 00:01:54,747
but if they seemed too busy to come,
I'd go over and put the order in.

44
00:01:54,814 --> 00:01:56,616
Bong-sik, are you like that too?

45
00:01:56,683 --> 00:01:59,252
He orders for me when we go out to eat.

46
00:01:59,319 --> 00:02:03,590
-He was way more introverted.
-Yes, he was more introverted than that.

47
00:02:03,656 --> 00:02:05,558
There was this word I wanted to say,

48
00:02:05,625 --> 00:02:08,394
but I never had enough courage
to say it out loud.

49
00:02:08,461 --> 00:02:11,064
-It's, "Auntie."
-"Auntie."

50
00:02:11,131 --> 00:02:12,932
-Yes, right.
-Some people say that all the time.

51
00:02:12,999 --> 00:02:16,269
I found that culture difficult
to adjust to at first.

52
00:02:16,336 --> 00:02:18,471
After all, she wasn't my family.

53
00:02:18,538 --> 00:02:20,273
Why do I have to call her auntie?

54
00:02:20,340 --> 00:02:21,407
-I get that.
-Yes.

55
00:02:21,474 --> 00:02:22,876
-I do too.
-It was awkward.

56
00:02:22,942 --> 00:02:26,079
Come to think of it, I still don't do it.
I can't call a server an auntie.

57
00:02:26,146 --> 00:02:29,082
I understand what you mean.
I couldn't push the bus stop buzzer.

58
00:02:29,149 --> 00:02:31,084
-Pushing the buzzer.
-Why did you feel shy about that?

59
00:02:31,151 --> 00:02:33,086
It felt like I was asking for attention.

60
00:02:33,153 --> 00:02:35,355
-I get it.
-You do?

61
00:02:35,421 --> 00:02:37,023
Even when I failed to get off,

62
00:02:37,090 --> 00:02:39,092
I couldn't ask the driver
to reopen the door.

63
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:41,594
-I totally get it.
-I'd go to the next stop and walk.

64
00:02:42,162 --> 00:02:43,496
When I was younger, I mean.

65
00:02:43,563 --> 00:02:45,565
-Chef Kang-rok nods.
-What if you go to the terminus?

66
00:02:45,632 --> 00:02:46,966
Can you relate to that, Chef Kang-rok?

67
00:02:47,901 --> 00:02:49,702
-I guess everyone was like me.
-Everyone?

68
00:02:49,769 --> 00:02:52,105
SHH! YOU DON'T HAVE TO SAY IT,
I ALREADY KNOW

69
00:02:52,172 --> 00:02:54,073
He's feeling closer on the inside.

70
00:02:54,140 --> 00:02:57,043
-It wasn't just him.
-It wasn't.

71
00:02:57,110 --> 00:03:01,014
Bong-sik and Suk-ku first became friends

72
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:04,951
-through a drama titled <i>D.P.</i>
-That was a good one.

73
00:03:05,018 --> 00:03:07,921
-I was the lieutenant colonel of the MP.
-The lieutenant colonel.

74
00:03:07,987 --> 00:03:10,156
You should've done a better job.
What happened?

75
00:03:10,223 --> 00:03:12,125
<i>And Suk-ku was a new captain.</i>

76
00:03:12,192 --> 00:03:15,195
I followed your order, sir.

77
00:03:15,261 --> 00:03:18,965
<i>We were both military officers,</i>
<i>so I'd give him direct orders</i>

78
00:03:19,032 --> 00:03:20,700
<i>-and harass him too.</i>
<i>-I see.</i>

79
00:03:21,801 --> 00:03:23,469
You don't have to take things this far.

80
00:03:23,536 --> 00:03:26,739
Was that before you two spoke casually
and were on first-name basis?

81
00:03:26,806 --> 00:03:29,475
At first, things were kind of awkward.

82
00:03:29,542 --> 00:03:31,444
It's the highest yet, right?

83
00:03:31,511 --> 00:03:33,947
We've worked together
in four different productions.

84
00:03:34,013 --> 00:03:36,482
-Is that so?
-Yes, so we've become very close.

85
00:03:36,549 --> 00:03:38,251
Among actors,

86
00:03:38,318 --> 00:03:39,953
he's known as the cheat code.

87
00:03:40,019 --> 00:03:42,288
We'd ask Bong-sik to help
when we'd face a difficult scene,

88
00:03:42,355 --> 00:03:45,558
-and he'd somehow make it work.
-I see.

89
00:03:45,625 --> 00:03:49,429
-We even said, "Bong-sik will save us."
-I see.

90
00:03:49,495 --> 00:03:51,030
That happened quite often.

91
00:03:51,097 --> 00:03:52,899
You have so much faith in him.

92
00:03:52,966 --> 00:03:54,701
There's a lot of faith and trust.

93
00:03:54,767 --> 00:03:55,935
Please continue a bit more.

94
00:03:58,071 --> 00:04:00,340
He's such a trustworthy actor.

95
00:04:00,406 --> 00:04:01,407
Thank you.

96
00:04:03,076 --> 00:04:06,613
There's a photo regarding <i>D.P.</i>
that became viral.

97
00:04:06,679 --> 00:04:07,714
Please show us.

98
00:04:08,948 --> 00:04:10,550
There it is. This one.

99
00:04:10,617 --> 00:04:14,520
It's a photo of Suk-ku, Bong-sik,
and Koo Kyo-hwan.

100
00:04:14,587 --> 00:04:16,756
<i>In D.P., they were</i>
<i>a lieutenant colonel, a captain,</i>

101
00:04:16,823 --> 00:04:18,491
<i>-and Kyo-hwan, a corporal.</i>
<i>-A corporal.</i>

102
00:04:18,558 --> 00:04:21,127
<i>But in real life,</i>
<i>Bong-sik is the youngest,</i>

103
00:04:21,194 --> 00:04:23,162
<i>and Kyo-hwan is the oldest.</i>

104
00:04:23,229 --> 00:04:26,132
Kyo-hwan was born in 1982,
then, 1983 and 1984.

105
00:04:26,199 --> 00:04:30,637
-It's the other way around.
-It went viral as a shocking photo.

106
00:04:30,703 --> 00:04:33,273
I guess I sensed something was off too.

107
00:04:33,339 --> 00:04:34,874
When I called Bong-sik casually,

108
00:04:34,941 --> 00:04:38,544
I thought,
"People may take me the wrong way."

109
00:04:38,611 --> 00:04:39,879
-"He's so rude."
-Yes.

110
00:04:39,946 --> 00:04:41,414
They might think he was older.

111
00:04:41,481 --> 00:04:42,882
When he's wearing a baseball jacket,

112
00:04:42,949 --> 00:04:45,752
he looks a bit more his age, but…

113
00:04:45,818 --> 00:04:48,121
-I put it on to look younger.
-I see.

114
00:04:48,187 --> 00:04:50,290
Your cap even says the year 1984.

115
00:04:50,356 --> 00:04:52,325
-He did.
-You're right.

116
00:04:52,392 --> 00:04:54,661
That's even more shocking.

117
00:04:54,727 --> 00:04:58,364
-He has the year of his birth on his cap.
-You're right.

118
00:04:58,431 --> 00:05:01,467
There's another photo
that went viral on social media.

119
00:05:01,534 --> 00:05:03,936
-Another one?
-Let's take a look.

120
00:05:04,003 --> 00:05:09,108
This was a photo Bong-sik uploaded
on his social media account for promotion.

121
00:05:10,043 --> 00:05:12,478
"My friends, you said you'd make
silly faces to make me look good."

122
00:05:12,545 --> 00:05:14,213
"Hashtag 84 meet-up."

123
00:05:14,280 --> 00:05:16,816
-It's a group of guys born in 1984?
-Who are the members?

124
00:05:16,883 --> 00:05:20,753
<i>Lee Jun-hyuk, Kim Yong-jun,</i>
<i>SE7EN, Simon Dominic…</i>

125
00:05:20,820 --> 00:05:22,288
<i>-Is that Yoo Yeon-seok?</i>
<i>-That's him.</i>

126
00:05:22,355 --> 00:05:23,923
It's a get-together with my friends.

127
00:05:23,990 --> 00:05:26,192
Here's a comment on that photo.

128
00:05:26,259 --> 00:05:27,360
Hey, don't read that.

129
00:05:27,427 --> 00:05:28,961
-What is it?
-It was hilarious.

130
00:05:29,028 --> 00:05:31,664
"Is this Teachers' Day?"

131
00:05:31,731 --> 00:05:32,965
BIG-NAME STUDENTS
AND THEIR TEACHER?

132
00:05:33,032 --> 00:05:35,234
-Teachers' Day.
-A teacher and his students?

133
00:05:35,301 --> 00:05:36,903
He's also sitting in the middle.

134
00:05:36,969 --> 00:05:40,473
-"They all gave him their time."
-Yes, giving you their time.

135
00:05:40,540 --> 00:05:42,175
He's sharing it himself now.

136
00:05:42,241 --> 00:05:44,210
They shared their time with you.

137
00:05:44,277 --> 00:05:47,013
-But he'll look younger in time.
-Yes.

138
00:05:47,080 --> 00:05:48,948
-You'll look the same.
-Just like this.

139
00:05:49,015 --> 00:05:51,250
Well, I kept looking older and older.

140
00:05:53,152 --> 00:05:55,521
I hear Bong-sik became

141
00:05:55,588 --> 00:05:58,124
the icon of positivity among Gen Z.

142
00:05:58,191 --> 00:06:02,895
I hear Hyun Bong-sik's thinking is
on the rise as a fad.

143
00:06:02,962 --> 00:06:05,832
-I recently heard it for the first time.
-But you have, right?

144
00:06:05,898 --> 00:06:08,334
They say it's how you take
your weaknesses and flaws,

145
00:06:08,401 --> 00:06:11,371
accept everything
without trying to cover it up,

146
00:06:11,437 --> 00:06:13,473
and even turn them into strengths.

147
00:06:13,539 --> 00:06:14,807
-Something like that.
-That's wonderful.

148
00:06:14,874 --> 00:06:16,876
So I broke those conventions

149
00:06:16,943 --> 00:06:19,278
and just did my own thing.

150
00:06:19,345 --> 00:06:21,781
It wasn't a huge deal or anything.

151
00:06:21,848 --> 00:06:24,584
It was just this concept
some people heard of.

152
00:06:24,650 --> 00:06:28,087
-It is a huge deal now.
-It is now.

153
00:06:28,154 --> 00:06:30,556
It's about to be
bigger than the lucky Vicky fad.

154
00:06:30,623 --> 00:06:32,191
-Lucky Bong-sik.
-Yes.

155
00:06:32,258 --> 00:06:33,793
-Do you know what lucky Vicky is?
-Yes.

156
00:06:33,860 --> 00:06:35,795
Then can you do "lucky Bong-sik"?

157
00:06:35,862 --> 00:06:37,463
We can get closer through this.

158
00:06:37,530 --> 00:06:39,165
Give us, "I'm totally lucky Bong-sik."

159
00:06:40,433 --> 00:06:42,668
Oh, no. I can't watch this.

160
00:06:42,735 --> 00:06:44,804
Bong-sik!

161
00:06:45,505 --> 00:06:47,974
Bong-sik, you have to do this
for us to get closer.

162
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:49,609
-"I'm totally lucky Bong-sik."
-"I'm totally lucky Bong-sik."

163
00:06:49,675 --> 00:06:53,746
Bong-sik! "I'm totally lucky Bong-sik."

164
00:06:53,813 --> 00:06:56,783
I'm totally lucky Bong-sik.

165
00:06:56,849 --> 00:07:00,019
HE'S DEFINITELY SWEET AND FRESH

166
00:07:00,787 --> 00:07:01,821
HE REALLY IS THE CHEAT CODE…

167
00:07:01,888 --> 00:07:03,322
Gosh, we got a preview ready.

168
00:07:04,991 --> 00:07:06,025
He's an actor, indeed.

169
00:07:06,092 --> 00:07:07,560
-He is.
-He's such an actor.

170
00:07:07,627 --> 00:07:10,229
He got it done in just one try.

171
00:07:10,296 --> 00:07:11,831
Suk-ku, can you do this too?

172
00:07:11,898 --> 00:07:14,567
No, I'm sweating so much
from just watching him

173
00:07:14,634 --> 00:07:17,670
that I probably have to redo my makeup.

174
00:07:17,737 --> 00:07:20,940
-I don't think I can do that.
-I see. You can't.

175
00:07:21,007 --> 00:07:24,977
-Anyway, Bong-sik. You don't even drink?
-No.

176
00:07:25,044 --> 00:07:27,346
Really? That's a big twist.

177
00:07:27,413 --> 00:07:28,481
Not even a drop?

178
00:07:28,548 --> 00:07:30,850
I've forced myself to have some,
but I threw up every time.

179
00:07:30,917 --> 00:07:32,351
It doesn't work in your system.

180
00:07:32,418 --> 00:07:34,353
It'd hurt my entire body too.

181
00:07:34,420 --> 00:07:36,556
Then what do you do when you two hang out?

182
00:07:36,622 --> 00:07:37,757
We eat.

183
00:07:37,824 --> 00:07:39,759
-You two eat?
-I rarely drink too.

184
00:07:39,826 --> 00:07:41,260
That's the secret to your smooth skin.

185
00:07:41,327 --> 00:07:44,096
I can drink a glass of soju

186
00:07:44,163 --> 00:07:45,932
-for over two hours.
-Whoa.

187
00:07:45,998 --> 00:07:49,535
-I barely wet my lips for two hours.
-Just touching it.

188
00:07:49,602 --> 00:07:51,137
Do you two hang out at coffee shops?

189
00:07:51,204 --> 00:07:52,405
Yes, we go to coffee shops.

190
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:53,773
I don't own a car.

191
00:07:53,840 --> 00:07:56,676
So I'm always grateful
that he comes and picks me up.

192
00:07:56,742 --> 00:07:58,211
-You don't own a car?
-You don't own a car?

193
00:07:58,277 --> 00:07:59,879
I just take taxis.

194
00:07:59,946 --> 00:08:03,049
You seemed like you'd own sports cars.
But you don't own a car?

195
00:08:03,115 --> 00:08:07,053
And I try to walk
within the radius of 5 km.

196
00:08:07,119 --> 00:08:09,455
THAT FAR?

197
00:08:09,522 --> 00:08:12,625
I usually walk
from Hannam-dong to Gaepo-dong area.

198
00:08:12,692 --> 00:08:13,860
SUK-KU TRAVELS…

199
00:08:13,926 --> 00:08:14,927
How does he do that?

200
00:08:14,994 --> 00:08:16,295
Have you had your car for a while?

201
00:08:16,362 --> 00:08:18,798
I once drove as a profession.

202
00:08:18,865 --> 00:08:20,066
-Really?
-Really?

203
00:08:20,132 --> 00:08:21,734
I was in the hourly chauffeur service

204
00:08:21,801 --> 00:08:23,636
and I've delivered rice too.

205
00:08:23,703 --> 00:08:24,704
Delivering rice?

206
00:08:24,770 --> 00:08:28,374
I think Bong-sik seems natural
in every role he plays

207
00:08:28,441 --> 00:08:31,143
because he has worked so many jobs before.

208
00:08:31,210 --> 00:08:32,745
He said that to make me look nice.

209
00:08:32,812 --> 00:08:37,083
But because I've had so many jobs
before I started my career,

210
00:08:37,149 --> 00:08:39,252
I thought I was a social misfit.

211
00:08:40,353 --> 00:08:41,621
I couldn't work one job for long.

212
00:08:41,687 --> 00:08:44,390
But it all added up
to help with your acting career.

213
00:08:44,457 --> 00:08:47,026
I knew you were totally lucky Bong-sik.

214
00:08:48,027 --> 00:08:49,562
We didn't have to make him do it.

215
00:08:49,629 --> 00:08:52,398
-You're totally lucky Bong-sik.
-All those difficult days

216
00:08:52,465 --> 00:08:55,101
-made him totally lucky Bong-sik.
-He's totally lucky Bong-sik.

217
00:08:55,167 --> 00:08:56,435
-Gosh.
-Gosh.

218
00:08:56,502 --> 00:08:57,670
Gosh.

219
00:08:58,938 --> 00:09:00,640
They're asking you to do it again.

220
00:09:00,706 --> 00:09:02,275
LOOKING OUT INTO THE DISTANCE

221
00:09:02,341 --> 00:09:04,410
Please run with it, Bong-sik.

222
00:09:04,477 --> 00:09:06,746
-Don't make me feel embarrassed.
-No.

223
00:09:06,812 --> 00:09:10,149
Bong-sik. Don't give him that.
Please do it one more time, Bong-sik.

224
00:09:10,216 --> 00:09:11,517
What do you think?

225
00:09:11,584 --> 00:09:14,387
-And the process made you what?
-What do you think, Bong-sik?

226
00:09:14,453 --> 00:09:17,657
-It made me totally lucky Bong-sik.
-Totally lucky Bong-sik.

227
00:09:18,491 --> 00:09:21,060
-It was all a process.
-He was lucky Bong-sik.

228
00:09:21,127 --> 00:09:22,995
<i>Chef & My Fridge</i> is a scary place.

229
00:09:23,062 --> 00:09:24,564
HE GOT THE CHEF & MY FRIDGE HAZING

230
00:09:24,630 --> 00:09:27,133
Please have a drink of that.

231
00:09:27,199 --> 00:09:29,468
Before we open his fridge,

232
00:09:29,535 --> 00:09:34,607
we'll find out what his orders are
and decide on the contenders.

233
00:09:34,674 --> 00:09:37,310
Let's see the orders. Show us.

234
00:09:37,376 --> 00:09:39,111
The first order is this.

235
00:09:39,178 --> 00:09:42,048
A dish with Hyun Bong Sixth Sense twist.

236
00:09:42,114 --> 00:09:43,249
Hyun Bong Sixth Sense.

237
00:09:43,316 --> 00:09:46,218
-A dish with Hyun Bong Sixth Sense twist.
-A dish with Hyun Bong Sixth Sense twist.

238
00:09:46,285 --> 00:09:48,287
