287
00:11:48,507 --> 00:11:51,043
and saw that Chef Yeon-bok had
the highest winning rate.

288
00:11:51,110 --> 00:11:52,645
-Exactly.
-That's right.

289
00:11:52,712 --> 00:11:54,880
I want to challenge myself
against the best.

290
00:11:55,514 --> 00:11:57,717
He's up against Chef Yeon-bok
after fighting Chef Sam last time.

291
00:11:57,783 --> 00:12:00,653
-It'll be a bloody fight.
-Yes.

292
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:04,523
They face this deadly match at the edge
of their demise after three losses!

293
00:12:04,590 --> 00:12:05,991
I'm not scared of losing.

294
00:12:06,058 --> 00:12:07,660
I WILL MAKE USE OF EVERYTHING!

295
00:12:07,727 --> 00:12:09,161
It feels like the holidays.

296
00:12:09,228 --> 00:12:10,362
-Whoa.
-What's wrong?

297
00:12:10,429 --> 00:12:11,564
-What's wrong?
-Whoa.

298
00:12:11,630 --> 00:12:12,832
He's on fire!

299
00:12:12,898 --> 00:12:14,500
What's wrong with this?

300
00:12:14,567 --> 00:12:16,268
-You still have time!
-This is crazy!

301
00:12:16,335 --> 00:12:18,104
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

302
00:12:18,170 --> 00:12:19,872
What am I going to do?

303
00:12:20,606 --> 00:12:22,608
I didn't know they'd take the whole thing.

304
00:12:22,675 --> 00:12:25,244
I'm missing a fridge at home,

305
00:12:25,311 --> 00:12:28,714
-so my place looks bigger now.
-I couldn't eat yesterday.

306
00:12:28,781 --> 00:12:32,651
It's now time to look
at Bong-sik's fridge.

307
00:12:32,718 --> 00:12:34,720
It looks much bigger than the fridge

308
00:12:34,787 --> 00:12:36,722
of a place with two brothers.

309
00:12:36,789 --> 00:12:39,258
When I used to lived
in a semi-basement unit,

310
00:12:39,325 --> 00:12:41,260
my friend in the neighborhood

311
00:12:41,327 --> 00:12:45,264
couldn't take his two-door refrigerator
when he moved, so he gave it to me.

312
00:12:45,331 --> 00:12:47,266
-I see.
-So I brought it home with a moving truck

313
00:12:47,333 --> 00:12:50,703
and began to use the two-door fridge
in that semi-basement unit.

314
00:12:50,770 --> 00:12:52,171
It opened up a whole new world.

315
00:12:52,238 --> 00:12:54,740
For example, when I stored veggies

316
00:12:54,807 --> 00:12:58,377
in the tiny fridge that was in the unit,
it'd be spoiled very easily.

317
00:12:58,444 --> 00:13:01,747
But it'd stay fresh
for even a week in that two-door fridge.

318
00:13:01,814 --> 00:13:03,215
I loved that so much.

319
00:13:03,282 --> 00:13:07,720
This fridge was the first one I bought,
something that wasn't handed down to me.

320
00:13:07,787 --> 00:13:10,256
-That's so significant.
-I see.

321
00:13:10,322 --> 00:13:14,026
-And now, we present Bong-sik's fridge!
-Bong-sik's fridge!

322
00:13:14,794 --> 00:13:16,562
EVERYONE IS AMAZED AT HIS FRIDGE

323
00:13:16,629 --> 00:13:17,630
First, a round of applause.

324
00:13:17,696 --> 00:13:19,064
-Bong-sik's fridge!
-Bong-sik's fridge!

325
00:13:19,632 --> 00:13:21,500
HIS FRIDGE LOOKS RATHER LOADED

326
00:13:21,567 --> 00:13:22,701
First, a round of applause.

327
00:13:23,869 --> 00:13:25,704
He lives alone,

328
00:13:25,771 --> 00:13:28,874
-but this deserves an A plus.
-He has so much stuff.

329
00:13:28,941 --> 00:13:30,910
You have lots of things.

330
00:13:30,976 --> 00:13:33,746
-You said you cooked at home, right?
-Yes.

331
00:13:33,813 --> 00:13:35,548
-I can tell that he lives alone.
-Why?

332
00:13:35,614 --> 00:13:38,450
Because he stores his eggs
in the container they came in.

333
00:13:38,517 --> 00:13:40,753
-Right.
-They're still in the container.

334
00:13:40,820 --> 00:13:42,188
-The eggs.
-Yes.

335
00:13:42,254 --> 00:13:44,089
-He has eggs.
-He has eggs.

336
00:13:44,156 --> 00:13:45,157
Beverages.

337
00:13:45,224 --> 00:13:47,526
Apple cider vinegar.

338
00:13:47,593 --> 00:13:48,994
-It's the ACV.
-Yes, ACV.

339
00:13:49,061 --> 00:13:50,429
It's the latest fad.

340
00:13:50,496 --> 00:13:52,231
Is that good for you?

341
00:13:52,298 --> 00:13:55,668
I'm just like you. I bought it
after seeing it on social media.

342
00:13:55,734 --> 00:13:58,571
Right? You bought it
after seeing it on social media.

343
00:13:58,637 --> 00:14:01,440
Was Bong-sik not allowed
to chase the trend?

344
00:14:01,507 --> 00:14:04,510
Well, I was just asking
if you always follow the trend.

345
00:14:04,577 --> 00:14:07,179
-Not always.
-So, that isn't always the case.

346
00:14:07,246 --> 00:14:09,548
I heard it can drop the blood sugar spike.

347
00:14:09,615 --> 00:14:13,519
He must like that because it's carbonated.

348
00:14:14,420 --> 00:14:17,323
You have meat in the fridge.

349
00:14:17,890 --> 00:14:20,526
I bought that
to make pork braised short ribs.

350
00:14:20,593 --> 00:14:22,895
-To make pork braised short ribs?
-To make pork braised short ribs?

351
00:14:22,962 --> 00:14:25,397
I see. You can make braised ribs?

352
00:14:25,464 --> 00:14:27,733
Do you prefer pork?

353
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:29,869
-No, I enjoy everything.
-Everything?

354
00:14:29,935 --> 00:14:31,537
-Beef, pork, and chicken.
-Yes.

355
00:14:31,604 --> 00:14:33,105
I LIKE ANY KIND OF MEAT

356
00:14:33,172 --> 00:14:36,208
Do you have trouble telling
