412
00:16:34,626 --> 00:16:38,130
My guests come, have a drink,
and leave whatever's left behind.

413
00:16:38,197 --> 00:16:40,566
You said alcohol hurts you.

414
00:16:40,632 --> 00:16:43,202
-Yes.
-But we just found five bottles of liquor.

415
00:16:45,471 --> 00:16:47,740
-This may be another liquor.
-Take a good look.

416
00:16:47,806 --> 00:16:49,408
-Right now…
-That's <i>omija</i>.

417
00:16:49,475 --> 00:16:51,577
So? How does it look, Detective Ahn?

418
00:16:51,643 --> 00:16:52,878
-It's <i>omija</i>.
-It is?

419
00:16:52,945 --> 00:16:54,780
I think there is a bit of soju in here.

420
00:16:56,382 --> 00:16:58,884
-I heard it was good for your throat.
-It is?

421
00:16:58,951 --> 00:17:01,320
He also stays on a diet.

422
00:17:01,387 --> 00:17:03,288
I see some boneless drumsticks.

423
00:17:03,355 --> 00:17:05,691
-Drumsticks?
-I don't like chicken breast.

424
00:17:05,758 --> 00:17:06,792
Boneless drumsticks.

425
00:17:06,859 --> 00:17:08,927
-Drumsticks?
-Drumsticks?

426
00:17:08,994 --> 00:17:11,930
-Shrimps.
-He has so many shrimps.

427
00:17:11,997 --> 00:17:14,366
Did you catch those in Suriname?
Why do you have so many?

428
00:17:15,134 --> 00:17:16,268
Are these from Suriname?

429
00:17:16,335 --> 00:17:18,337
-There are five large packs
-That's a lot.

430
00:17:18,404 --> 00:17:19,738
-that he bought.
-Do you like shrimp?

431
00:17:19,805 --> 00:17:22,241
I throw those in when I make <i>aglio e olio</i>.

432
00:17:22,307 --> 00:17:23,575
Do you make pasta too?

433
00:17:23,642 --> 00:17:25,077
-What?
-Pasta?

434
00:17:25,144 --> 00:17:27,079
Was Bong-sik not allowed to make pasta?

435
00:17:27,746 --> 00:17:30,149
See? Something seems off.
I felt like that too.

436
00:17:30,682 --> 00:17:32,951
-So you make pasta too.
-Yes.

437
00:17:33,018 --> 00:17:36,321
You have a lot of bread in here.

438
00:17:36,388 --> 00:17:40,159
I use that baguette
when I make <i>gambas al ajillo</i>.

439
00:17:40,225 --> 00:17:41,894
I slice it up and eat it with that.

440
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:43,228
Do you make <i>gambas al ajillo</i> too?

441
00:17:43,295 --> 00:17:44,596
There's a meal kit next to it.

442
00:17:45,564 --> 00:17:46,799
He cooks a lot.

443
00:17:46,865 --> 00:17:50,602
Was Bong-sik not allowed to make
<i>gambas al ajillo</i>?

444
00:17:51,170 --> 00:17:54,706
WHAT'S SO WEIRD ABOUT BONG-SIK
AND GAMBAS AL AJILLO?

445
00:17:55,340 --> 00:17:57,509
You all need to drop your prejudices!

446
